HEADWORD: Notability
<hw>Not`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Notabilities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>notabilit⟦eacute⟧</ets> .]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Quality of being
notable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A notable, or remarkable, person or thing; a person
of note.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Parisian <xex>notabilities</xex>⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A notable saying.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notable</ent>⟦br⟧
